# RuneLite Plugin – OSParty Conventions

## Project Overview
- **Plugin**: `OSPartyPlugin` (`net.osparty`) – lets players advertise, search, and join parties.
- **Build**: Gradle wrapper (`./gradlew`). Java 11 source/target, JDK 21 runtime.
- **Run client**: `./gradlew runClient` (launches RuneLite with the plugin loaded).

## Package Structure
```
net.osparty/
  OSPartyPlugin.java      ← main plugin class (@PluginDescriptor)
  OSPartyConfig.java      ← config interface (@ConfigGroup)
  api/                    ← HTTP clients (PartyApiClient, PartyService)
  model/                  ← plain data classes (Party, Applicant, Activity…)
  party/                  ← RuneLite party-bus messages & LiveParty
  runewatch/              ← RuneWatch scammer-check integration
  ui/                     ← Swing panels (OSPartyPanel, SearchPanel…) & overlays
```

## Key RuneLite Patterns

### Plugin Class
```java
@Slf4j
@PluginDescriptor(name = "OSParty", description = "...", tags = {...})
public class OSPartyPlugin extends Plugin {
    @Inject private Client client;
    @Inject private OSPartyConfig config;
    @Inject private ClientThread clientThread;  // for client-thread work
    @Inject private OverlayManager overlayManager;

    @Provides
    OSPartyConfig provideConfig(ConfigManager manager) {
        return manager.getConfig(OSPartyConfig.class);
    }

    @Override protected void startUp() throws Exception { ... }
    @Override protected void shutDown() throws Exception { ... }
}
```

### Event Subscriptions
```java
// Always annotate with @Subscribe; never poll in startUp loops.
@Subscribe
public void onGameTick(GameTick event) { ... }

@Subscribe
public void onGameStateChanged(GameStateChanged event) { ... }
```

### Scheduled Tasks
```java
// Use @Schedule instead of Timer/ScheduledExecutorService.
@Schedule(period = 5, unit = ChronoUnit.SECONDS, asynchronous = true)
public void pollPartyStatus() { ... }
```

### Config Interface
```java
@ConfigGroup(OSPartyConfig.GROUP)
public interface OSPartyConfig extends Config {
    String GROUP = "osparty";

    @ConfigItem(keyName = "myKey", name = "Display name", description = "...", position = N)
    default boolean myKey() { return true; }
}
```

### Swing / UI Thread Safety
- Build and mutate Swing components only on the EDT.
- Use `SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -> ...)`.
- Use `clientThread.invokeLater(() -> ...)` for RuneLite client-thread work.

### Overlays
```java
// Implement Overlay, register/deregister in startUp/shutDown.
overlayManager.add(myOverlay);   // startUp
overlayManager.remove(myOverlay); // shutDown
```

### Lombok
- `@Slf4j` for logging (`log.debug/info/warn/error`).
- `@Data`, `@Value`, `@Builder` for model classes.
- `@Getter`/`@Setter` on fields to avoid boilerplate.

## RuneLite Party Bus
Messages extend `PartyMember` or implement `PartyData`:
```java
// Sending
partyService.send(new MyMessage(...));

// Receiving
@Subscribe
public void onMyMessage(MyMessage msg) { ... }
```

## Do / Don't

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|---------|
| Use `@Subscribe` for game events | Poll game state in loops |
| Use `clientThread` for client reads | Read client state on EDT directly |
| Deregister overlays in `shutDown` | Leave overlays registered after plugin stops |
| Use `ImageUtil.loadImageResource` | Load images with `ImageIO` directly |
| Format config descriptions clearly | Leave `description` blank |
